column2: As your guest at court, §Y[Root.GetTitledName]§! can be sent away if [Root.GetSubjectPronoun] is not your prisoner or working for you in an official capacity.
A direct vassal of my liege, §Y[Root.Liege.GetBestName]§!, is my rightful de jure vassal. All of us are at peace.\n
Is NOT Guardian of a child.\n
§Y[Root.GetTitledFirstName]§! will be banished from your court and forced to take up residence somewhere else in your realm. [Root.GetSubjectPronounCap] will be very unlikely to return.\n\n

§Y[Root.GetTitledFirstName]§! will be banished from your court and, because [Root.GetSubjectPronoun] is of a different faith, will try to leave your realm for one of [Root.GetObjectPronoun] own religion. [Root.GetSubjectPronounCap] will be very unlikely to return.\n\n
